Received these pics a few days ago from my buddy @justs93 over at @justracing702 and I’m even more stoked for this drift truck build 🔥

If y’all remember the YouTube video, I’m doing a full K-series build for my 75 Datsun 620. It’ll be sleeved, full arp, complete rod + piston, head work, etc etc. (I’ll go into more detail once I get to the power train section of the build)
Just know that this is not only going to be fast as hell (maybe faster than the Z?) but also a sliding machine.. can’t wait to show y’all all the stuff… keep ya eyes peeled and appreciate you guys for still being here waiting for the updates. ❤️

🔥Step 2 of the Datsun pickup build🔥
____
Finally accumulated enough parts to get the #240sx rear end retrofitted onto this Datsun 620 pick up. Ain’t gonna lie, it’s going to be a challenge but I think the end results is going to be worth it💯
____
Decided to go with the @silverminemotors  dual caliper set up kit by @wilwooddiscbrakes for that EZ rear lock up paired up with wilwood hydro ebrake and massive brake power since we’re going to try and push 600-700 whp out of the K24A built by @justracing702 🤘🏼
____
Control arms by @gktech_official for that sleek look and extra clearance, rest of the suspension is by @isrperformance (PRO version) to handle all the beating this thing is going to take at the drift track.
____
Can’t wait for this build to be done boys, it’s going to be one for the books for sure, I’ll be vlogging the entire process on @youtube so keep an eye out for the build videos, and remember to sub!!! ✌🏼
____

It’s gonna be nuts!🔥
